## Decisions log

When making a significant technical or product choice, log it in `docs/DECISIONS.md` using the format defined there. <!-- OPTIONAL: active_decisions_line — include if include_decisions_active == true --> If the decision creates a binding constraint not visible from reading code alone, also mirror a one-liner into `docs/DECISIONS_ACTIVE.md`.

<!--
The per-decision mirror criterion is the load-bearing part. A decision belongs in DECISIONS_ACTIVE.md only if ALL of the following hold: (a) it imposes a rule the agent must follow now, (b) the rule is not enforced or visible by reading the code itself, (c) it has not been superseded by a later decision. Apply the test decision-by-decision; do not bulk-mirror DECISIONS.md. Bulk mirroring degrades the file's signal — when every decision is "active," none of them are, and the agent stops reading.

Working positive example: field-society-demo correctly curates 3 of 9 decisions into DECISIONS_ACTIVE.md (D-006 no-auth, D-007 AI scope, D-008 Claude-interprets-form), each defensible against the three-condition criteria. The five it omitted are visible from data, non-binding, future-scope, executed, or visible from package.json — the criterion ruled each out on first read. The discipline holds without skill enforcement when applied carefully.
-->

A decision is significant if:

- it would surprise a future session that hadn't seen it made
- it ruled out an obvious alternative
- it affects a core workflow
- it touches a safety default

Do not log every small implementation detail. Log the calls that matter.

