## Path-scoped rules in `.claude/rules/`

Modular rules with `paths:` frontmatter that auto-load when matching files are read. **Claude Code honors `paths:` automatically.** Always-on rules (no `paths:` field) load every session.

**For Codex and other tools that don't honor `paths:` natively:** at session start, read every file in `.claude/rules/`. Each rule has a `paths:` frontmatter (or none, for always-on rules). When you open or edit a file, mentally check which rules' `paths:` match and treat their content as if loaded.

Always-on rules: `git-and-deploy.md`, `session-discipline.md`<!-- OPTIONAL: , `product-rules.md` -->.

