## Before you respond — load-bearing constraints

These are the rules that must not be lost mid-session. Read this block last so it stays in attention. Items here meet the bar: violating them damages product, loses work, or burns a stakeholder. Other rules (direct-on-main, no deploy CLI, reproduce-before-fixing) live in the body of this file and are not duplicated here — they are already at the top in "Primary constraints" and in their own rule files. Duplication dilutes the signal.

1. **Hard scope limits.** Bug fix or small tweak: ≤ 3 files, ≤ 50 lines. Feature: ≤ 300 lines per session. File size cap: 500 lines. Detail: `.claude/rules/session-discipline.md`.
<!-- OPTIONAL: visual_confirmation_recency — include if uses_visual_confirmation_gate == true. Renumber remaining items contiguously when dropped. -->
2. **Visual confirmation gates the commit.** Do not commit UI changes until <!-- PARAMETERIZE: visual_confirmer_name --> confirms in a running dev server. Detail: `.claude/rules/session-discipline.md`.
<!-- OPTIONAL: ai_constraint -->
3. **Never call the AI layer from a client component.** Always route through an API route. Detail: `.claude/rules/ai-shared.md`.
<!-- OPTIONAL: vocabulary_constraint -->
4. **Vocabulary lock applies.** Use only the canonical names listed above. Detail: `AGENTS.md` "Vocabulary lock" section.

If any constraint above conflicts with a request, surface the conflict before acting.
